{"title_page": "Norbert Jacques", "text_new": "{{short description|Luxembourgish novelist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        = Norbert Jacques by Waldemar Flaig 1927.jpg\n| name         = Norbert Jacques\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date|1880|6|6|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Eich, Luxembourg|Luxembourg-Eich]], Luxembourg\n| death_date   = {{Death date and age|1954|5|15|1880|6|6|df=y}}\n| death_place  = [[Koblenz]], [[West Germany]]\n| occupation   = Screenwriter\n| yearsactive  = 1922\u20131954\n}}\n\n'''Norbert Jacques''' (6 June 1880 \u2013 15 May 1954) was a Luxembourgish novelist, journalist, and [[screenwriter]] who wrote in German. He was born in [[Eich, Luxembourg|Luxembourg-Eich]], [[Luxembourg]] and died in [[Koblenz]], [[West Germany]]. He created the character [[Dr. Mabuse]] who was a feature of some of his novels, including \"Mabuse's Colony\". Jacques is known best for his work for [[cinema of Germany|German cinema]]. He is credited with writing the scripts for 16 films made between 1922 and 1990. In 1922 he received German citizenship.\n\n==Novels==\n* ''Dr. Mabuse, der Spieler'' (1921)\n* ''Mabuses Kolonie'' (1930, fragment)\n* ''Das Testament des Dr. Mabuse'' (1932)\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Dr. Mabuse the Gambler]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[Man Against Man (1924 film)|Man Against Man]]'' (1924)\n* ''[[The Bordello in Rio]]'' (1927)\n* ''[[The Testament of Dr. Mabuse]]'' (1933)\n* ''[[Final Destination: Red Lantern]]'' (1960)\n* ''[[Scotland Yard Hunts Dr. Mabuse]]'' (1963)\n* ''[[The Secret of Dr. Mabuse]]'' (1964)\n* ''[[Dr. M (film)|Dr. M]]'' (1990)\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0415167|Norbert Jacques}}\n\n{{Doctor Mabuse}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jacques, Norbert}}\n[[Category:1880 births]]\n[[Category:1954 deaths]]\n[[Category:German screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian journalists]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian novelists]]\n[[Category:German journalists]]\n[[Category:German male journalists]]\n[[Category:Male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:German male novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century German novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century German male writers]]\n\n\n{{Screen-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Luxembourgish novelist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        = Norbert Jacques by Waldemar Flaig 1927.jpg\n| name         = Norbert Jacques\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date|1880|6|6|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Eich, Luxembourg|Luxembourg-Eich]], Luxembourg\n| death_date   = {{Death date and age|1954|5|15|1880|6|6|df=y}}\n| death_place  = [[Koblenz]], [[West Germany]]\n| occupation   = Screenwriter\n| yearsactive  = 1922\u20131954\n}}\n\n'''Norbert Jacques''' (6 June 1880 \u2013 15 May 1954) was a Luxembourgish novelist, journalist, and [[screenwriter]] who wrote in German. He was born in [[Eich, Luxembourg|Luxembourg-Eich]], [[Luxembourg]] and died in [[Koblenz]], [[West Germany]]. He created the character [[Dr. Mabuse]] who was a feature of some of his novels, including \"Mabuse's Colony\". Jacques is known best for his work for [[cinema of Germany|German cinema]]. He is credited with writing the scripts for 16 films made between 1922 and 1990. In 1922 he received German citizenship.\n\n==Novels==\n* ''Dr. Mabuse, der Spieler'' (1921)\n* ''Mabuses Kolonie'' (1930, fragment)\n* ''Das Testament des Dr. Mabuse'' (1932)\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Dr. Mabuse the Gambler]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[Man Against Man (1924 film)|Man Against Man]]'' (1924)\n* ''[[The Bordello in Rio]]'' (1927)\n* ''[[The Testament of Dr. Mabuse]]'' (1933)\n* ''[[Final Destination: Red Lantern]]'' (1960)\n* ''[[Scotland Yard Hunts Dr. Mabuse]]'' (1963)\n* ''[[The Secret of Dr. Mabuse]]'' (1964)\n* ''[[Dr. M (film)|Dr. M]]'' (1990)\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0415167|Norbert Jacques}}\n\n{{Doctor Mabuse}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jacques, Norbert}}\n[[Category:1880 births]]\n[[Category:1954 deaths]]\n[[Category:German screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian journalists]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian novelists]]\n[[Category:German journalists]]\n[[Category:German male journalists]]\n[[Category:Male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:German male novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century German novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century German male writers]]\n\n\n{{Screen-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norbert_Jacques"}
